        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add pagination support for drive list and info",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFeishu drive list/info missing pagination support\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/drive-schema.ts`: Add page_size, page_token, and all parameters\n- `extensions/feishu/src/drive.ts`: Add pagination loop for listFolder and getFileInfo\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Feishu drive list and info actions lacked pagination, failing when folders contain more than 10 items (the default page size).\n\nReal environment tested: ubuntu-24.04, Node 24, branch fix/issue-93928-feishu-drive-pagination.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n  node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/feishu/src/drive.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/test-projects.mjs extensions/feishu/src/drive.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n RUN  v4.1.8\n\n ✓ forwards list pagination cursors and returns continuation metadata\n ✓ searches subsequent drive pages for info while preserving folder scope\n ✓ registers feishu_drive and handles comment actions\n ✓ defaults add_comment file_type to docx when omitted\n ... (17 tests total, all passing)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  17 passed (17)\n   Duration  6.52s\n```\n\nPagination-specific tests pass, verifying:\n- List pagination cursors are forwarded across pages\n- Subsequent drive pages are searched for file info\n- Continuation metadata is returned correctly\n- Folder scope is preserved across paginated lookups\n\nObserved result after fix: All 17 drive tests pass, including the two pagination-specific tests that verify the has_more + page_token loop. The pagination logic matches the existing pattern used elsewhere in the codebase.\n\nWhat was not tested: End-to-end with a real Feishu tenant with >10 items in a folder (requires platform-specific credentials).\n\nCloses: #93928",
